const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/commercial/fryer-repair/filter-system-issues/";

const title = "Commercial Fryer Filter System Issues LA — Same Day";
const description = `Built-in fryer filter not working? Pump motor, pump seal, hose, paper jam, control board. Frymaster FilterQuick, Pitco, Henny Penny, Vulcan. $120 dx.`;

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Why does my Frymaster FilterQuick keep showing 'filter error'?",
    a: "Frymaster FilterQuick uses an integrated filter pump and a digital controller; the system displays an error code when something interrupts the normal filter cycle. Common causes ranked by frequency: (1) filter paper installed wrong (folded incorrectly, blocking pump intake), (2) pump motor failed, (3) pump seal leaking, causing pressure loss, (4) filter pan not seated properly (microswitch detects pan position; if not seated, system aborts), (5) control board fault. We diagnose with the Frymaster service manual and bring common parts on the van."
  },
  {
    q: "How often should the filter system pump be replaced?",
    a: "Filter pump motors run a duty cycle of 1-3 minutes per filter cycle, several times a day, in a hot oil environment with thermal cycling. Year 5-8 is typical replacement window for most built-in filter pumps (Frymaster FilterQuick, Pitco filter drawer, Henny Penny filter pump). Pump seals (which fail before the motor itself) at year 4-7 typical. Pump motor replacement runs $640-920 typical all-in including the part. Pump seal replacement (without full motor swap) $360-540."
  },
  {
    q: "Can I run the fryer without the built-in filter?",
    a: "Short-term yes, with caveats. The fryer's heating function operates independently of the filter system, so the fryer will cook normally while the filter is down. The caveat: oil quality degrades faster without daily filtering, which means you'll be replacing oil more frequently and possibly seeing slow recovery times within a week of operating without filtering. Restaurants typically can't afford to operate more than 2-3 days without filtering on a high-volume fryer. We respond same-day on filter system service for that reason."
  },
  {
    q: "What's the difference between built-in filtration and external filter machines?",
    a: "Built-in filtration (Frymaster FilterQuick, Pitco filter drawer integrated into the fryer cabinet, Henny Penny pressure-fryer filter system) uses a filter pump and pan housed within the fryer itself. External filter machines (FryFilter, Filtaclean, Restaurant Technologies oil management service) are standalone units rolled up to each fryer for daily filtering. We service both. Built-in systems are more convenient for daily filtering; external machines have advantages for multi-fryer kitchens that want a single filter for the whole battery. Service approach is similar: diagnose pump, seals, hoses, electrical."
  },
  {
    q: "What does a typical filter system repair cost?",
    a: "Diagnostic is $120, applied to repair. Common repairs: filter paper jam clearing + pump test (no parts) $200-260; pump seal replacement $360-540; pump motor replacement $640-920; filter hose replacement $260-380; filter pan microswitch $200-340; control board fault diagnosis $440-680 if board replacement is needed. Most filter system calls resolve at $360-680 all-in. Pump motor replacement is the high end at year 5-8."
  },
  {
    q: "My fryer pumps oil out but won't pump it back in.",
    a: "Common Frymaster FilterQuick symptom that points to a specific failure: the discharge pump runs but the return cycle fails, leaving the fryer empty after a filter attempt. Three usual causes. (1) Filter paper saturated or folded incorrectly, blocking return flow. Replace paper, fold per Frymaster spec, retest. (2) Return-side hose kinked or hose check valve stuck, restricting return flow. (3) Pump capacity reduced (early-stage pump failure that still discharges but can't pull return through the filter resistance). We diagnose by observing the cycle and measuring pump differential."
  },
  {
    q: "Do you do PM contracts for filter systems?",
    a: "Yes. High-volume restaurant fryers benefit from quarterly preventive maintenance on the built-in filter system: pump motor inspection, seal condition check, hose inspection, microswitch test, control board firmware check (where applicable). Quarterly PM costs less than a single emergency filter call and prevents most of the unscheduled service we see. Quote-based depending on the number of fryers and the brand mix."
  }
];

