<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">01 · Built-in filter systems we service</p>
    <h2>Brand-specific architectures.</h2>

    <h3 class="cause-h3">Frymaster FilterQuick (industry-dominant in QSR chains)</h3>
    <p>Frymaster's FilterQuick is the integrated filter system on most current Frymaster RE Series and FilterQuick units. Pump-driven filter cycle: oil discharges from the vat through a filter pan with replaceable paper, then returns to the vat post-filtration. Digital controller with diagnostic codes. We see this brand in chain QSRs (McDonald's, Burger King, Carl's Jr., KFC partnerships) and high-volume independent restaurants. Common service items: pump seal year 4-7, pump motor year 5-8, filter paper jamming from operator error, microswitch on pan position, return-side check valve, control board faults.</p>

    <h3 class="cause-h3">Pitco filter drawer (built into Solstice and Solstice Supreme)</h3>
    <p>Pitco's filter drawer is integrated into the cabinet base on Solstice and Solstice Supreme open-vat fryers. Pump-driven cycle similar to FilterQuick architecture but with brand-specific control panel layout and pan design. Common service items match the FilterQuick pattern: pump seal year 4-7, pump motor year 5-8, filter paper installation issues, drawer position microswitch.</p>

    <h3 class="cause-h3">Henny Penny filter pump (pressure fryer)</h3>
    <p>Henny Penny 600 series pressure fryers have integrated filter systems specific to pressure-fryer architecture. Filter cycle is interlocked with the pressure cycle so that filtering can only occur with the cooking chamber depressurized. Common service items: pump seal failure (year 5-8 typical for the heavier-duty pressure-fryer pump), filter hose deterioration (more frequent than open-vat due to pressure-cycle stress), pressure release interlock fault.</p>

    <h3 class="cause-h3">Vulcan integrated filtration (LG and CE Series)</h3>
    <p>Some Vulcan LG (gas) and CE (electric) units include integrated filtration. Less feature-dense than Frymaster FilterQuick but reliable. Common service items: pump seal, hose, filter pan condition.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">02 · Common filter system failures</p>
    <h2>Six failure modes ordered by frequency.</h2>

    <h3 class="cause-h3">1. Filter paper installation error (about 15-20% of calls, no parts)</h3>
    <p>Filter paper folded incorrectly, installed upside-down, or torn during installation blocks the pump intake or causes excessive pressure drop. Symptom: pump runs but filter cycle aborts, system displays error, oil doesn't fully filter or doesn't return. Resolution: re-install paper per the manufacturer's spec, retest. We train operator staff on correct installation if recurring. About 15-20% of filter calls resolve at $200-260 with paper re-installation, no parts.</p>

    <h3 class="cause-h3">2. Pump seal failure (year 4-7 typical)</h3>
    <p>The pump seal between motor shaft and pump body fails from continuous heat exposure and thermal cycling. Symptom: oil leaking from the pump area, reduced pump capacity (slow filter cycle, incomplete return), or pump motor seizing if oil ingresses into the bearing. Replacement runs $360-540 all-in. We catch this often during quarterly PM before it becomes an emergency.</p>

    <h3 class="cause-h3">3. Pump motor failure (year 5-8 typical)</h3>
    <p>The pump motor wears from duty-cycle loading and heat exposure over years. Symptom: motor doesn't run when the filter cycle starts, motor runs but produces no flow (impeller issue), motor runs intermittently or trips overload. Diagnostic with multimeter on motor windings and visual on impeller. Replacement runs $640-920 all-in. Year 5-8 is typical replacement window across the major brands.</p>

    <h3 class="cause-h3">4. Filter hose deterioration (year 6-9)</h3>
    <p>The flexible hoses connecting pump to filter pan and pan to vat-return develop cracks, kinks, or fitting leaks over time. Symptom: oil leaking under the filter unit, reduced flow, error code from pressure drop. Replacement runs $260-380 typical.</p>

    <h3 class="cause-h3">5. Microswitch on filter pan position</h3>
    <p>Filter systems include a microswitch detecting whether the filter pan is fully seated; if not seated, the system aborts the filter cycle (safety + cleanliness). Microswitch failures present as system refusing to filter even with the pan in place. Replacement runs $200-340.</p>

    <h3 class="cause-h3">6. Control board fault</h3>
    <p>The digital controller managing filter cycle timing, pump operation, and error display can fail at year 8+ from accumulated thermal cycling. Symptom: error codes that don't match observable system condition, system locks in an error state, controller display unresponsive. Replacement runs $640-920 depending on brand and model. Less common than the mechanical failures above; we check easier causes first.</p>
  </div>
</section>

